Acquiring a new customer can cost five times more than retaining an existing customer. Increasing customer retention by 5% can increase profits from 25-95%.

A web-based tool for telecom companies to predict which customers might leave and to provide helpful insights. This platform uses advanced AI models to give real-time predictions on customers at risk of leaving. By combining data from different sources, the tool creates useful information about customer behavior. This allows companies to spot trends and tackle potential problems early. As a result, companies can create targeted plans to keep customers, offer personalized experiences, and take steps to boost customer satisfaction and lower churn rates.







SUPERVISOR: DR. ADNAN IDRIS

FIZA MAQSOOD . HIRA ABSAR KHAN. HADEESA MUSKAAN



concatenation with original dataset



synthetic samples generated



balanced dataset


telecom dataset

unbalanced distribution of chuners and non churners

data preprocessing



generative adversial network



Training and evaluating the model



Churn prediction and business insights



TELECOM CHURN PREDICTION USING

GENERATIVE AI

ABSTRACT

PREDICTEL- PREDICT. DETECT. RETAIL

  • Churn Prediction: Predicts customers at risk of leaving.
  • Real-Time Insights: Provides live monitoring of customer behavior.
  • Data Integration: Combines multiple data sources for comprehensive analysis.
  • Tailored Strategies: Helps design targeted plans to reduce churn and enhance satisfaction.

The main navigation contains buttons for document level options. To switch between buttons, use the left and right keys and to activate, press Enter. To skip to the canvas, press “Ctrl+F2”.
Canvas
The canvas is where your design is. To navigate into the page, press Enter. To navigate into groups or elements on the page, press Enter again. Press tab to move to the next page, group, or element. To operate the toolbar, use the “Ctrl+F1” key. If an element is selected, move it using the arrow keys; rotate using the “,” key and “.” key; and resize using the arrow keys with the “Ctrl” key. All of these keys can be modified with the “Shift” key to increase increment.
